    "summary": "I am an experienced academic economist specializing in the research fields of international business (firm productivity, competitiveness, multinationals), corporate finance (private equity, leveraged buyouts, institutional investors), and international finance (international investments; financial side of economic integration; micro/macro aspects of economic fluctuations; history of globalization). \n\nDuring the corona-crisis I innovated and successfully redesigned a large-scale graduate lecture class and a small-scale practical seminar class into fully online-based courses using various online education techniques and the online applications the BigBlueButton (bigbluebutton.org) and Zoom (zoom.us) web conferencing systems, Panopto (panopto.com) online video platform, and implemented online exam with ANS (www.ans.app) learning platform. From 2021, I started to serve as the Bachelor Program Coordinator in Economics and Business Economics and International Bachelor at Erasmus School of Economics.\n\nBesides the extensive expertise in data analysis and common financial databases, I gained a deep knowledge of administrative micro-databases ORBIS and AMADEUS, by Bureau Van Dijk  (a Moody's company), covering millions of companies globally. With my co-authors, I wrote ORBIS manuals on how to construct nationally representative firm level panels of ownership and financial information, usable for research purposes.\n\nMy other expertise includes corporate valuation, securing research and policy grants, policy advisory work, managing individual researchers and teams, and teaching and supervision of bachelor, master, and doctoral students.\n\nI served as a visiting scholar at the National Bank of Ukraine and the research department of the International Monetary Fund, Washington D.C. In 2016-18, I participated in the grant for the European Commission (in cooperation with PricewaterhouseCoopers and Eurostat) Key Enabling Technologies (KETs) Observatory Phase II to develop/update the methodology and data collection for tracing the deployment of KETs in the EU and other regions. \n\nI am open to career opportunities as\n1. Permanent full professor or visiting professor at a research university.\n2. A consultant / researcher position at a research/policy organization or think tank to conduct research or lead research efforts in my fields of expertise.\n3. Visiting teaching position at a finance or economics department to teach the large scale or seminar-(under)graduate classes on corporate finance and valuation, international finance, macroeconomics, and monetary economics.",
