            "description": "As one of my outreach activities in 2016-2018, I contributed to successful completion of the project \"Key Enabling Technologies (KETs) Observatory Phase II\" for the Executive Agency for Small and Medium-sized Enterprises (EASME) and the DG GROW - Directorate-General for Internal Market, Industry, Entrepreneurship and SMEs of the European Commission (the EU's Ministry of Economy) in cooperation with PricewaterhouseCoopers (PwC).                                                                                                               \n\nThe overall objective of the second phase of KETs Observatory is to continue providing business stakeholders, as well as European and national and regional policy makers with reliable, regularly updated and comprehensive data and analysis on the deployment of KETs. Specifically, the KETs Observatory will be promoted as a practical tool for the elaboration and implementation of Smart Specialization Strategies in the EU regions, providing valuable insights into the performance of the EU regions in terms of industrial deployment of KETs and thus helping regional stakeholders with their entrepreneurial discovery process.\n\nWithin this project, I developed the new methodology (see https://ec.europa.eu/growth/tools-databases/kets-tools/kets-observatory/methodology ) and organized the data collection for tracing the deployment of KETs in the EU and other regions. ",
